    "The architecture of the generator's network is depicted in the figure below, which was proposed by Radford et al.",
    "for his research on using deep convolutional adversarial generative networks for unsupervised representation learning.",
    "Key Feature:• Instead than using all-maximum pooling, one should use convolutional stride.• Use transposed convolution for up sampling.• Extricate completely connected layers.• Employ batch normalisation in all layers excluding the discriminator's input and output layers.",
    "• To avoid using tanh in the output, you should use ReLU in the generator.• The discriminator should make advantage of LeakyReLU.",
